# Payments And Ledger Invariants

- Preserve the append-only ledger model. New payment and transaction behavior should add entries and events rather than mutating historical records in place.
- Treat monetary values in the core payments and ledger path as satoshis stored in integer types (`long` in Java, `BIGINT` in Postgres).
- Keep business flow orchestration in application services and keep persistence and network details behind ports and adapters.
- New async payment or transaction workflows should follow the existing outbox pattern: persist an outbox event and let the outbox job publish it.
- Define and reuse Kafka topics through `KafkaTopics` (outbox / producers) and `KafkaTopicNames` (`@KafkaListener`, header comparisons); do not introduce ad hoc topic string literals.
- Preserve idempotency protections around transaction references and account ledger entries unless a feature explicitly changes those guarantees.
- When adding database changes in this area, use Flyway migrations and preserve existing uniqueness and consistency constraints unless the feature intentionally changes them.

